Technology Brief -- Sierra On-Line Inc.:
   Development Costs Blamed
   For Quarterly Drop in Net
Net income in the third fiscal quarter ended Dec. 31 was
$2.6 million, or 45 cents a share, exceeding analysts'
expectations of 43 cents a share vs. year-ago net of $2.6
million, or 47 cents a share. Sales jumped 23% to $16.4
million from $13.3 million.
   Separately, the company said that it plans to offer 1.5
million shares of common to fund development of the Sierra
Network, among other purposes.